cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on object detection in traffic scenes using a real-time object detection framework. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions the framework's capability in autonomous driving. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the improvements made to the YOLOv1 framework in YOLOv2. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a pre-trained model for object detection. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss any natural language processing techniques used in the framework or in the evaluation of the results.
